{
    "esm": "0.4.0",
    "metadata": {
        "name": "LayerPhaseChangeEnergy",
        "description": "Per-layer phase change energy for the urban canopy snow/soil thermodynamics: the energy required to change a single layer's ice mass from w_ice_n at time n to w_ice_np1 at time n+1 over time step Δt (Oleson et al. 2010 Eq. 4.73). Migrated from UrbanCanopy.jl@9200edd4 src/roof_wall_road_snow_temperatures.jl:1037 (`LayerPhaseChangeEnergy` @component). The column-summed output of this component over all layers is the E_p_layers input of `TotalPhaseChangeEnergy` (Eq. 4.72). Parameterized as observed-only: w_ice_n, w_ice_np1, Δt are inputs (parameters); E_p is the algebraic output.",
        "tags": [
            "urban_canopy",
            "snow",
            "temperatures",
            "phase_change",
            "observed-only",
            "clmu"
        ],
        "created": "2026-05-06T00:00:00Z",
        "authors": [
            "UrbanCanopy.jl contributors",
            "EarthSciModels migration (mdl-sqzs)"
        ],
        "references": [
            {
                "citation": "Oleson, K. W., et al. (2010). Technical Description of version 4.0 of the Community Land Model (CLM). NCAR Technical Note NCAR/TN-478+STR. Chapter 4, Section 4.6 (Snow Hydrology — per-layer phase change energy), Eq. 4.73, p. 106."
            }
        ]
    },
    "models": {
        "LayerPhaseChangeEnergy": {
            "reference": {
                "notes": "source_ref: UrbanCanopy.jl@9200edd4f15609f20339d3a7d104de8064544310:src/roof_wall_road_snow_temperatures.jl:1037\nUpstream `LayerPhaseChangeEnergy` is an MTK `@component` whose three inputs (w_ice_n, w_ice_np1, Δt) are `@parameters` and whose single output (E_p) is a time-indexed `@variable` with one algebraic equation (Eq. 4.73). Identical equation structure preserved here.\n\nThe upstream component declares one `@constant`: L_f (latent heat of fusion, 3.337e5 J/kg, Oleson Table 1.4). It is encoded here as a parameter with the upstream value as default — the same convention used by sibling component snow_melt_no_layers.esm for its `L_f` literal. The output is the latent-heat conversion of the per-step ice mass change scaled by Δt — the simplest single-equation algebraic component in the urban canopy temps suite.\n\nObservability classification: this component is functionally observed-only — the single output variable is given by a single algebraic equation in terms of the parameters (and the `(t)` time index has no role since there is no derivative). Test scenarios use `time_span: [0, 1]` and sample at t=0 to mirror the convention used by sibling observed-only ESM files in this rig (total_phase_change_energy.esm, snow_melt_no_layers.esm, snow_capping_runoff.esm).\n\nTolerance rationale (model-level rel=1e-9): observed-only single-equation algebraic system (no ODE integration); the equation is one subtraction, one product, and one division, so roundoff is at the IEEE-754 ULP level (~1e-16). 1e-9 leaves comfortable headroom above ULP roundoff and matches the convention used by sibling observed-only files (total_phase_change_energy.esm uses 1e-9 for the analogous additive-identity equation of Eq. 4.72). Tighter `abs: 1e-12` is asserted on outputs that are exactly zero by construction so the assertion does not silently accept a stuck-at-1e-3 regression."
            },
            "tolerance": {
                "rel": 1.0e-9
            },
            "variables": {
                "w_ice_n": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "kg/m^2",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Ice mass at time n"
                },
                "w_ice_np1": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "kg/m^2",
                    "default": 0.0,
                    "description": "Ice mass at time n+1"
                },
                "Δt": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "s",
                    "default": 1.0,
                    "description": "Time step"
                },
                "L_f": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "J/kg",
                    "default": 3.337e5,
                    "description": "Latent heat of fusion of water (Oleson et al. 2010 Table 1.4 — 3.337e5 J/kg)"
                },
                "E_p": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "W/m^2",
                    "description": "Phase change energy for layer (Oleson Eq. 4.73): L_f * (w_ice_n - w_ice_np1) / Δt"
                }
            },
            "equations": [
                {
                    "lhs": "E_p",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "/",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    "L_f",
                                    { "op": "-", "args": ["w_ice_n", "w_ice_np1"] }
                                ]
                            },
                            "Δt"
                        ]
                    }
                }
            ],
            "tests": [
                {
                    "id": "upstream_melting",
                    "description": "Reproduces upstream `LayerPhaseChangeEnergy - Melting` test (UrbanCanopy.jl test/roof_wall_road_snow_temperatures_test.jl:1200). Inputs: w_ice_n = 10, w_ice_np1 = 8 (2 kg/m^2 melted), Δt = 3600 s. E_p = 3.337e5 * 2 / 3600 ≈ 185.389 W/m^2 (positive, melting branch). Anchors fidelity to the upstream Julia component at the same parameter values.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "w_ice_n": 10.0,
                        "w_ice_np1": 8.0,
                        "Δt": 3600.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "E_p", "time": 0.0, "expected": 185.38888888888889 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "upstream_no_change",
                    "description": "Reproduces upstream `LayerPhaseChangeEnergy - No Change` test (UrbanCanopy.jl test/roof_wall_road_snow_temperatures_test.jl:1224). Inputs: w_ice_n = w_ice_np1 = 10, Δt = 3600 s. E_p = 0 by exact cancellation in the (w_ice_n - w_ice_np1) factor — exercises the no-phase-change limit of Eq. 4.73.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "w_ice_n": 10.0,
                        "w_ice_np1": 10.0,
                        "Δt": 3600.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "E_p", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-12 } }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "freezing_branch",
                    "description": "Freezing-branch sign check: when w_ice_np1 > w_ice_n (water → ice in the layer over Δt), the latent heat is released to the layer and E_p is negative. Inputs: w_ice_n = 10, w_ice_np1 = 12, Δt = 3600 s. E_p = 3.337e5 * (-2) / 3600 ≈ -185.389 W/m^2. Verifies that the equation is sign-preserving and that no spurious clamp/abs has been introduced (the upstream component has no `max(..., 0)` guard on E_p — the floor is applied downstream by SnowMeltNoLayers' M_1S, not here).",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "w_ice_n": 10.0,
                        "w_ice_np1": 12.0,
                        "Δt": 3600.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "E_p", "time": 0.0, "expected": -185.38888888888889 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "complete_melt_short_dt",
                    "description": "Complete melt of a 5 kg/m^2 layer in a 30-minute step (Δt = 1800 s). w_ice_n = 5, w_ice_np1 = 0 → E_p = 3.337e5 * 5 / 1800 ≈ 926.944 W/m^2 — exactly the high-melt threshold value of sibling SnowMeltNoLayers' `exact_full_melt` test (Δt = 3600, W = 10) by symmetry of the L_f * Δw / Δt expression. Exercises the all-melt-in-one-step regime.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "w_ice_n": 5.0,
                        "w_ice_np1": 0.0,
                        "Δt": 1800.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "E_p", "time": 0.0, "expected": 926.9444444444445 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "small_mass_short_dt",
                    "description": "Sub-cycling regime: thin ice film (w_ice_n = 0.001 kg/m^2 ≈ 1 g/m^2) with half melted in a 1-minute substep. w_ice_n = 1.0e-3, w_ice_np1 = 5.0e-4, Δt = 60 s → E_p = 3.337e5 * 5e-4 / 60 ≈ 2.781 W/m^2. Verifies the small-mass / short-Δt regime that arises when the per-layer phase-change calculation is called from a sub-cycling outer loop.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "w_ice_n": 1.0e-3,
                        "w_ice_np1": 5.0e-4,
                        "Δt": 60.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "E_p", "time": 0.0, "expected": 2.7808333333333333 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "daily_step",
                    "description": "Daily-step regime (Δt = 86400 s): a 20 kg/m^2 daily ice loss (w_ice_n = 50, w_ice_np1 = 30) yields a small daily-mean E_p ≈ 77.245 W/m^2 — reflective of the time-averaged latent flux from a sustained warm-spell melt event. Exercises the long-Δt limit at the opposite extreme of `small_mass_short_dt`.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "w_ice_n": 50.0,
                        "w_ice_np1": 30.0,
                        "Δt": 86400.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "E_p", "time": 0.0, "expected": 77.24537037037037 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "all_zero",
                    "description": "All-zero parameters: w_ice_n = w_ice_np1 = 0 with default Δt = 1 s. E_p = 3.337e5 * 0 / 1 = 0 by construction (no ice, no phase change). Exercises the trivial-mass limit and confirms the equation does not divide-by-zero or produce NaN at the all-zero point of parameter space.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "w_ice_n": 0.0,
                        "w_ice_np1": 0.0,
                        "Δt": 1.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "E_p", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0, "tolerance": { "abs": 1.0e-12 } }
                    ]
                }
            ],
            "examples": [
                {
                    "id": "E_p_curve_vs_w_ice_np1",
                    "description": "Sweep w_ice_np1 across the freezing-through-melting range with w_ice_n = 10 kg/m^2 and Δt = 3600 s held fixed. E_p = L_f * (10 - w_ice_np1) / 3600 — a unit-slope (with sign) line crossing zero at w_ice_np1 = 10 (no change), positive (melting) for w_ice_np1 < 10, and negative (freezing) for w_ice_np1 > 10. Surfaces Eq. 4.73 directly.",
                    "initial_state": {
                        "type": "per_variable",
                        "values": {}
                    },
                    "parameters": {
                        "w_ice_n": 10.0,
                        "Δt": 3600.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "w_ice_np1",
                                "range": { "start": 0.0, "stop": 20.0, "count": 21, "scale": "linear" }
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "E_p_curve",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "E_p vs w_ice_np1 (w_ice_n = 10, Δt = 3600): linear with negative slope, zero-crossing at w_ice_np1 = w_ice_n.",
                            "x": { "variable": "w_ice_np1", "label": "w_ice_{n+1} (kg/m^2)" },
                            "y": { "variable": "E_p",       "label": "E_p (W/m^2)" }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "two_d_sweep_dw_dt",
                    "description": "Joint sweep over w_ice_np1 and Δt at fixed w_ice_n = 10 kg/m^2. Surfaces the inverse-Δt scaling of Eq. 4.73: for a given Δw, halving Δt doubles E_p. Iso-energy contours are 1/Δt curves (hyperbolic) in the (Δw, Δt) plane.",
                    "initial_state": {
                        "type": "per_variable",
                        "values": {}
                    },
                    "parameters": {
                        "w_ice_n": 10.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "w_ice_np1",
                                "range": { "start": 0.0, "stop": 20.0, "count": 11, "scale": "linear" }
                            },
                            {
                                "parameter": "Δt",
                                "range": { "start": 60.0, "stop": 3600.0, "count": 11, "scale": "linear" }
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "E_p_heatmap",
                            "type": "heatmap",
                            "description": "E_p as a function of w_ice_np1 and Δt: iso-energy contours follow constant L_f * Δw / Δt — hyperbolic in Δt for fixed Δw.",
                            "x": { "variable": "w_ice_np1", "label": "w_ice_{n+1} (kg/m^2)" },
                            "y": { "variable": "Δt",        "label": "Δt (s)" },
                            "value": { "variable": "E_p", "reduce": "final" }
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
    }
}
